        " الْأَذَانُ تَرْتِيلٌ وَ الْإِقَامَةُ حَدْرٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A group of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Muhammad Bin Sinan, from Al Hassan Bin Al Sariy, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The <span class=\"iTxt\">Azān</span> is recited slowly, but the <span class=\"iTxt\">Iqamah</span>, flowingly’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "26. A group of our people has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from Muhammad ibn Sinan from al-Hassan ibn al-Sariy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Adhan is said with Tartil (articulation slowly) and ‘Iqamah is said quickly.’” "
        ]
      }
